The U.S. Justice Department is also investigating Binance for money laundering. Binance has also, in the last two years, upset <a href="https://www.theblock.co/linked/103143/german-finance-regulator-issues-warning-about-binances-stock-tokens-offering" data-v-f87c67ca="">regulators in other countries</a> such as <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/109766/uk-fca-bans-crypto-exchange-binance" data-v-f87c67ca="">the U.K.</a>, Germany and the Netherlands. <br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
Meanwhile, in recent years, Binance has <a href="https://www.theblock.co/linked/98038/binance-hires-former-senate-finance-committee-chair-regulator" data-v-f87c67ca="">hired several veterans</a> of financial regulation, compliance and criminal investigation. Whether or not the company, now armed with a host professionals experienced in compliance, can turn the page and earn the confidence of international and national regulators remains to be seen.&nbsp;
